oceanofdarkstars,
After laughing uncontrolled for about an hour, I'll give you the answer you need:

1. Most e-mail providers don't allow files over 10MB's to be sent as attachments, this is 10GB's.

2. Even if someone sent it to you as an e-mail, it would force you to download it from the slow mail-server instead. So there wouldn't be any point at all to do so.

3. Torrents can be resumed, shared between multiple people at the same time and it's a lot faster, easier and more sane than sending anything at all over 10Megs by e-mail.

I'd recommend you get yourself at least a DSL connection, which you can get pretty cheap nowdays since there's a lot of competitive providers.
